      oracle.apps.fnd.appltest.diagfwk.engine.DiagCmdRunTests
All Implemented Interfaces:
DiagConstants, DiagCmdConstants
public class DiagCmdRunTests
extends DiagCmd<TestRun>

Command for running one or more tests. The following parameters are supported:

  • test - a single test name or a "," separated list of test names. When specifying a single test name you can also specify one or more input parameter names and values using the "input:" parameter.
  • app - One or more "," comma separated list of product codes e.g. FND,GL as specified in the Applications taxonomy.
  • modid - One or more "," comma separated list of module IDs specified in the Applications taxonomy.
  • modkey - One or more "," comma separated list of module keys specified in the Applications taxonomy.
  • tag:[tag name]=[tag value] - Name of a tag specified in the diagnostics test repository and a Value for the tag specified in the diagnostics test repository.
  • runName - A name for the current run. If not specified, a default run name is generated.
  • recurse - Y/N. If Y, runs all tests associated with the specified taxonomy modules and/or diagnostic tags. If N, runs only the tests immediately associated with the specified taxonomy modules and/or diagnostic tags. The default value is Y.
  • prereq - Y/N. If Y, performs a prerequisite analysis to identify any prerequisite tests and runs those prior to running the specified tests. If N, runs only the specified tests. The default value is N.
  • moninterval - Monitoring interval (in seconds). Specifies the interval in seconds in which the monitoring threads will update test execution status to the test repository. Default value is 30 seconds.
  • nthreads - Number of parallel threads to use in order to execute tests. Default value is 5.
  • input:[param name]=[param value] - The "input:" option is only applicable when running a single test using the "test" option. One or more parameter names and values for those paramters can be specified using this option.
  • execmode - This is a hidden argument used only by the engine in order to indicate the client that invoked the run. possible values are 'C' - for command line. 'U' - for local UI. 'B' - for batch program etc.
This command will return a TestRun object representing the test executed test run. If the "waitForCompletion" parameter was set to "Y", the returned TestRun object is fully populated with all the executed test executions. However if the "waitForCompletion" parameter was set to "N" (this is the default behaviour), the TestRun object is returned as soon as the execution is kicked off and may not contain completion information. In such cases, the TestRun object will contain a run ID (GUID) that can be used by the client to track the status of the run.
